0.2.1
  - added Logs tab
0.2.0
  - SDUI (Server-Driven UI) integration — full plugin UI via Resonance SDUI framework
  - Added get_ui() returning a Page with five tabs: Status, Devices, Settings, Advanced, About
  - Added handle_action() dispatcher for: activate, deactivate, restart, save_settings,
    delete_device, toggle_device, update_device
  - Status tab: bridge status badge, key-value info, activate/deactivate/restart buttons
  - Devices tab: table with inline-editable name column, enable/disable toggle, delete actions,
    per-device settings modal with General/Audio/Behaviour tabs
  - Settings tab: form with binary select, interface/server inputs, auto-start/logging/debug
    toggles, conditional debug category/level selects (visible_when)
  - Advanced tab: read-only view of common options from bridge XML config (collapsible card)
  - About tab: markdown card with plugin description and links
  - Added [ui] section to plugin.toml (enabled=true, sidebar_label="AirPlay", sidebar_icon="cast")
  - Per-device advanced overrides: sample_rate, codecs, resample, alac_encode, encryption,
    send_metadata, send_coverart, mute_on_pause, auto_play, idle_timeout
  - UX polish: collapsible cards, inline-editable table columns, device settings modal (lg size)
  - Registered UI and action handlers in setup() via ctx.register_ui_handler/register_action_handler

0.1.0
  - Migrated to Resonance community plugin repository
  - Binaries no longer bundled; downloaded on-demand from philippe44/LMS-Raop
  - Cleaned up logging (use %s formatting instead of f-strings)
  - Plugin uses PluginContext.server_info for squeeze2raop server address
  - Tests adapted: ensure_binary mocked, platform-independent path assertions
  - Added plugin.toml manifest

0.0.1
  - Initial development by Pinoatrome
  - Moved to plugin framework
  - Added pytest suite
  - Added squeeze2raop configuration (XML parse/dump)
  - Added raopbridge plugin preferences (JSON settings)
  - Added squeeze2raop executable management
  - Added PID file and logging (category/levels)
  - Added GNU General Public License, version 2
  - Generate squeeze2raop config file in interactive mode
  - Added plugin commands and REST API
  - Added plugin settings view
  - Added registered device listing
  - Added device management (add/update/remove)
  - Evaluate server slimproto endpoint exposed to the plugin
  - POC to use squeeze2raop pre-built native executable in Python
